<p>The <code>until</code> tag provides looping until a condition becomes true (opposite of while).</p>

<h2>Basic Until Loop</h2>
<pre>{open}set counter=1{close}
{open}until $counter > 5{close}
  Item {open}$counter{close}
  {open}increment $counter{close}
{open}/until{close}</pre>
<p>Result:</p>
{set counter=1}
<ul>
{until $counter > 5}
  <li>Item {$counter}</li>
  {increment $counter}
{/until}
</ul>

<h2>Count Up Until</h2>
<pre>{open}set n=0{close}
{open}until $n eq 5{close}
  {open}$n{close}
  {open}increment $n{close}
{open}/until{close}</pre>
<p>Result: {set n=0}{until $n eq 5}{$n} {increment $n}{/until}</p>

<h2>Comparison: while vs until</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>while</th>
    <th>until</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Loops while condition is TRUE</td>
    <td>Loops while condition is FALSE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><code>{open}while $x < 5{close}</code></td>
    <td><code>{open}until $x >= 5{close}</code></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Equivalent results:</td>
    <td></td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>while $x < 3: {set x=0}{while $x < 3}{$x} {increment $x}{/while}</p>
<p>until $x >= 3: {set x=0}{until $x >= 3}{$x} {increment $x}{/until}</p>
